{{Sexagenary cycle comprehensive}}
'''Yang Water Tiger also known as <!--please transliterate all the hiragana readings into romaji and provide the kanji--> Yang Water Tiger''' (壬寅, みずのえとら、じんすいのとら、じんいん) is one element of the {{ill|Sexagenary Cycle Comprehensive|ja|Sexagenary cycle comprehensive|12=draft}}.

It is the 39th combination in the Sexagenary Cycle Comprehensive, preceded by {{ill|Xin Chou|ja|辛丑|12=draft}} and followed by {{ill|Gui Mao|ja|癸卯|12=draft}}. In the {{ill|Yin-Yang and Wuxing Theory|ja|陰陽五行思想|1=Yin-Yang and Wuxing Theory|12=draft}}, the {{ill|Heavenly Stems|lt=Ten Heavenly Stems|ja|十干|12=draft}}'s {{ill|Ren|ja|壬|1=Mizunoe (壬)|12=draft}} represents yang water, while the {{ill|Twelve Earthly Branches|ja|十二支|12=draft}}'s {{ill|Tiger|ja|寅|1=Tiger (zodiac)|lt=Tiger (寅)|12=draft}} represents yang wood, forming a mutual generation (water generates wood) according to the principles of the Five Elements.

