{{Sexagenary cycle comprehensive}}
'''Yang Water Tiger also known as  Yang Water Tiger''' (壬寅, みずのえとら、じんすいのとら、じんいん) is one element of the {{ill|Sexagenary Cycle Comprehensive|ja|Sexagenary cycle comprehensive|12=draft|12=draft}}.

It is the 39th combination in the Sexagenary Cycle Comprehensive, preceded by {{ill|Xin Chou|ja|辛丑|12=draft|12=draft}} and followed by {{ill|Gui Mao|ja|癸卯|1=Yin Water Rabbit|12=draft|12=draft}}. In the {{ill|Yin-Yang and Wuxing Theory|ja|陰陽五行思想|1=Yin-Yang and Wuxing Theory|12=draft|12=draft}}, the {{ill|Heavenly Stems|lt=Ten Heavenly Stems|ja|十干|12=draft|12=draft}}'s {{ill|Ren|ja|壬|1=Mizunoe (壬)|12=draft|12=draft}} represents yang water, while the {{ill|Twelve Earthly Branches|1=Earthly Branches|lt=Twelve Earthly Branches|ja|十二支|12=draft|12=draft}}'s {{ill|Tiger|ja|寅|1=Tiger (zodiac)|lt=Tiger (寅)|12=draft|12=draft}} represents yang wood, forming a mutual generation (water generates wood) according to the principles of the Five Elements.

== Yang Water Tiger Year ==
A {{ill|Common Era|ja|西暦|1=Common Era|2=ja|3=西暦|4=zh|5=公元|6=es|7=Era común|8=nl|9=Gangbare jaartelling|10=simple|11=Common Era|12=draft|12=draft}} year that leaves a remainder of 42 when divided by 60 is considered a Yang Water Tiger {{ill|year|ja|年|12=draft|12=draft}}.
